cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.DL. 

This paper is about automatic generation of Chinese poetry, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel iterative framework that utilizes a Quality-Aware Masked Language Model, which involves deep learning and neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves training and optimization of the model, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also involves the use of encoder-decoder structures, which is a common technique in deep learning and falls under cs.DL (Deep Learning).
